  "transcript": "Every relationship has three stages.\r\nMost people only experience the first two.\r\nStage one. Everything feels beautiful.\r\nThe texts feel exciting. The flaws feel cute.\r\nYou feel chosen. This is the stage where love feels easy.\r\nThen comes stage two. This is where reality shows up.\r\nYou start noticing habits you ignored before.\r\nSmall things start to bother you.\r\nEgos clash. Effort feels uneven.\r\nThis is the stage where most relationships end.\r\nNot because love disappears,\r\nbut because it starts asking for patience instead of excitement.\r\nBut if two people choose to stay,\r\nto listen instead of react,\r\nto work together instead of walking away,\r\nthey reach stage three.\r\nThis is where love becomes calm.\r\nArguments don't turn into wars.\r\nSilence doesn't feel scary.\r\nYou don't need to prove anything anymore.\r\nYou don't fall in love everyday.\r\nYou choose each other everyday.\r\nAnd that's the stage people call real love.",
